SIMPLE: clypeate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clypeate
<hw>Clyp"e*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>clupeatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>clupeare</ets> to arm with a shield,
fr. <ets>clupeus</ets>, <ets>clipeus</ets> shield.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Shaped like a round buckler or shield;
scutate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Furnished with a shield, or a
protective plate or shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clypeiform</ent>⟦br⟧
